# Quantum-Observer-Simulator-Wave-Particle-Duality-Wavefunction-Collapse
This project provides a highly accurate interactive simulation of the fundamental quantum mechanical phenomena observed in the double-slit experiment. By bridging classical wave optics with quantum measurement theory, the simulator demonstrates the transition between wave-like interference and particle-like probability distributions.
# Quantum Observer Simulator

This interactive tool simulates the double-slit experiment, visualizing wave-particle duality. It demonstrates quantum interference and wavefunction collapse upon observation. 

Users can adjust slit separation (d) and width (a) to explore how measurement fundamentally alters quantum outcomes. Built for educational and research analysis.
